race.description: Jim, Tess And Jamie Irving Memorial Mdn Plate
race.comment: SOOTY AND SWEEP (8) improved sharply at his second outing, beaten 2L at Albury over 1400m, taking time to muster. He's still a work in progress, but the step up in trip suits and he maps well. Has weight relief, and it's hard to risk the potent McDougall-Scott linkage. MR MAGNIFICENCE (7) went forward over 1600m at Canberra and held on well beaten 1.7L. Has a low gate and will be suited around here. Expect him to be up to this challenge. TIME FOR SNOW (12) rates well off the narrow defeat at Wagga over a mile. Will present at peak fitness and will get his chance. HONEST WARRIOR (6) settled well back over the mile at Canberra. Ran his best race at Queanbeyan prior and may be the best of the remainder.
